children.name: get_version
children.comment: Return a PEP 440-compliant version number from VERSION.

children.name: update
children.comment: Extend rather than replace existing key lists.

children.name: get_bytes_from_wsgi
children.comment:
Get a value from the WSGI environ dictionary as bytes.

key and default should be strings.

children.name: _get_response
children.comment:
Resolve and call the view, then apply view, exception, and
template_response middleware. This method is everything that happens
inside the request/response middleware.

children.name: copy
children.comment: Return a mutable copy of this object.

children.name: _load_post_and_files
children.comment: Populate self._post and self._files if the content-type is a form type

children.name: build_absolute_uri
children.comment:
Build an absolute URI from the location and the variables available in
this request. If no ``location`` is specified, build the absolute URI
using request.get_full_path(). If the location is absolute, convert it
to an RFC 3987 compliant URI and return it. If location is relative or
is scheme-relative (i.e., ``//example.com/``), urljoin() it to a base
URL constructed from the request variables.

children.name: process_request
children.comment:
Check for denied User-Agents and rewrite the URL based on
settings.APPEND_SLASH and settings.PREPEND_WWW

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
When the status code of the response is 404, it may redirect to a path
with an appended slash if should_redirect_with_slash() returns True.

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
If request.session was modified, or if the configuration is to save the
session every time, save the changes and set a session cookie or delete
the session cookie if the session has been emptied.

children.name: process_response
children.comment:
Update the storage backend (i.e., save the messages).

Raise ValueError if not all messages could be stored and DEBUG is True.
